BFN 

<F P=106> [By correspondent Kim In-kyu from Washington] </F>
  [Text] The North Korean mission to the United Nations on 27 
May notified the National Press Club, a U.S. media organization, 
that North Korean President Kim Il-song cannot accept its 
invitation. Pak Kil-yon, ambassador of the North Korean mission 
to the United Nations, wrote in a letter sent to the chairman of 
the National Press Club that he is thankful that the National 
Press Club had invited President Kim Il-song to the luncheon 
address, however, President Kim Il-song cannot attend the 
luncheon address due to his busy schedule. 

